column1: Table 4: Components of population change by administrative area, mid-2017 to mid-2018
1) Area codes refer to the 2018 Council areas and 2018 NHS Board areas.

2) Population estimates for mid-2017 are based on the 2011 Council areas and 2014 NHS Board areas, whereas mid-2018 population estimates are based on the 2018 Council areas and    2018 NHS Board areas. The 2018 Council areas and 2018 NHS Board areas differ from the previous areas due to a small boundary change at Keltybridge (which did not affect the population), between Fife and Tayside.

3) Estimated net civilian migration includes movements within Scotland, the rest of the UK and overseas. Moves to and from armed forces are included in 'other changes'.
Net migration totals of have been rounded to the nearest ten at administrative area level, and the nearest hundred at national level. This may result in the sum of administrative area data differing from the national totals.
4) Includes changes in the number of prisoners, armed forces stationed in Scotland and a rounding adjustment.
